## [V5.3.0] — 2026-03 — The Cognitive Architecture Mega-Patch

### Added
- Phase-Gate Protocol for DEV_MODE high-strain payloads (hard stop after roadmap).
- Guided Pruning (softened SNR Rule — isolate anomalies before hard context reject).
- Anchor Override transparency (`[ANCHOR OVERRIDE: {Persona}]` output).
- Safety Veto transparency (`[SAFETY VETO: Unanimous Consent]` output).
- Document Integrity Mandate (no patch-level splicing, dynamic markdown collision wrappers).
- Rejection Ledger (Changelog Protocol for abandoned concepts: Premise / Failure Mode / Revival Condition).
- Mode Supremacy (DEV_MODE overrides VECTOR_SYNC committee locks).
- Theory Mode Override (mutual exclusion between Section 9 and Section 10).
- Kill Condition Lock (Meta-Updates require unanimous GUARDRAIL_SEC + INTERNAL_JUDGE consent).

### Changed
- Salience Hierarchy: replaced non-core "ALWAYS" imperatives with gated IF/THEN logic.
- CTRL_COMPRESS redefined as attention-management protocol (not token management).
- Multi-AI systemic integration: consolidated peer-reviews from Claude, DeepSeek, Perplexity, Z.ai, ChatGPT.

